# Li World Studio (vision guardrails)

**Canonical plan:** `docs/game-dev/world-studio-vision.md`

When designing game dev, editor, or world-creation features:

## Product direction

- **AI-first:** every feature must be reachable via **stable agent APIs** (`studio.commands.*`), not menu-only.
- **Local models default:** Ollama/llama.cpp-class; cloud requires explicit `raises Net` + audit.
- **Above Unity/Unreal on workflow:** diffable Li worlds + `lic build` proof — not “clone UE5 renderer first.”
- **Read like prose:** imports `world`, `scene`, `physics.runtime`, `studio.ui` — see `li-readability-philosophy.mdc`.

## Module rules

| Need | Package | Do not |
|------|---------|--------|
| Editor shell | `li-studio` (new) | Dump editor into `lic` compiler |
| World/biomes | `li-world` (new) | Encode worlds only in binary |
| Assets | `li-assets` (new) | Hardcode paths in compiler |
| AI tools | `li-studio-ai` (new) | Silent cloud calls |
| Scene graph | **expand** `li-scene` | Fork second scene system |
| UI chrome | **expand** `li-ui` | Adopt opaque UI framework without Li bindings |
| Physics | **expand** `li-physics-*` | Unproved C++ physics in user path |

## Phases (PH-GD)

Work in order unless issue says otherwise: **GD-1** studio MVP → **GD-2** world model → **GD-3** AI loop → **GD-4** assets → **GD-5** render → **GD-6** scale → **GD-7** player.

## Agents

- Proposals that touch >1 repo: update master plan + this vision doc section.
- Reference SOTA in PR (what we replicate/improve); add bench or `li-tests/game_dev/` row.
- **No** default work in `li-demo` for studio features.
